<br>
Cleric = Heals, Buffs, Stuns<br>
Enchanters = Clarity, Buffs, Speeds, Nukes<br>
Shamans = Speeds, Sows, Buffs, Slows<br>
Necro = Dots, Fear, Snares, Nukes<br>
Druid = Sow, Snare, Dots, Nukes, Heals, Ports<br>
Wizards = Snare, Nukes, Root, Ports<br>
Bard = What can't they do?<br>
Tanks = Learn the pet parking tactic and the tank will never be hit<br>
Magician = Nukes, Damage Shields, Chain casting pets<br>
<br>
As you can easily see any of the above offers plenty for a partnership.  You've just got to learn how to effictively work with whatever class you have and you can see exp.  <br>
<br>
For a partner if I have preference I think I'll almost always choose another mage that knows what he is doing.  (As the ones I know do)  My personal favorite group though is acutally a trio that I leveled with for quite a few levels.  Mage, Mage, Necro. <p><a href=mailto:Zaknafinis@Hotmail.com>Zaknafinis Convoquer (54th level Elementalist)</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uailees.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ailees</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ikebana-toulouse.com/styles/rose.jpg BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 65<br> <font color=#333333>(3/29/01 9:34:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=192.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.ikebana-toulouse.com/styles/seika4t.jpg width=102 height=145></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Best partner for a mage?</span><hr size=1> I love to fight with a <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Rogue</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->.<br>
of course he must know how to fight using pet as main tank.<br>
