</FONT></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uezno.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ezno</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/posticons/eyes.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 379<br> <font color=#333333>(3/29/01 11:55:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=192.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Best partner for a mage?</span><hr size=1> <br>
I'd say the Necro is the best overall single partner for a Mage. They are another pet class (adding in an additional tank) and thier spell lineup is just about the opposite of ours, giving the duo a lot of power and variety.  There's the obvious fear kiting, but also the mini-healing, mez, etc, of the necro that comes in handy while we have the ability to summon weapons for the necro pet and provide a fast burndown when needed.  At 51 I teamed with a 53 necro in SF and we spent 4 hours of constant pulling there.. most downtime was about 30 seconds after a bad pull of 4 (which we whiped out systematically).<br>
<br>
Second best I'd go with a Druid.  Snare/SoW/Ports/healing good mix of other skills.   <br>
<br>
Third would be a cleric. A Mage/Cleric combo is probably the most powerful in terms of what you can take down (you can take down some major stuff with a cleric complete healing your fire pet as that massive dmg shield beats the crap out of the MoB) but there is more downtime than with the necro combo.  <p> <br>
