<br><img src="http://www.interplay.com/icewind/images/EarthElemental.gif"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ukylere.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kylere</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 87<br> <font color=#333333>(3/29/01 4:00:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=192.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Best partner for a mage?</span><hr size=1> 1. Enchanter: Nukes, slows on target, Crack, their own pet which is easy to engage, they just tash and sit at mobs feet a sec, crowd control if needed after all lets face it mages are the best single mob fighters that exist, but 2-3 can be deadly. I pull to pet, chanter adds his pet, then slows the mob, then if needed Malise line, then we sit back, both pets damage shielded and sped makes short work.<br>
