In difficult ground, press on; In encircled ground, devise strategems; In death ground, FIGHT! - Sun Tzu</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uabmagfab.showPublicProfile?language=EN>AbMagFab</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 155<br> <font color=#333333>(3/29/01 9:54:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=192.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Best partner for a mage?</span><hr size=1> You have to look at what we are and what we don't have.  We are fast damage dealers.  We don't have any damage control or defense.  So while any class is a good partner for a mage (looking at it the other way around, a mage is a good partner for any class), some combos are better.<br>
<br>
Crowd control is one of the more critical holes for us.  Necros, Druids, Wizzies, and Chanters all provide this.<br>
<br>
Other defense is also something critical we don't have.  Like snaring, fear, healing, stunning.  Same group as above.<br>
<br>
For my money, Necro/Mage is a great 2 person team outdoors.  Fear kiting, 2 pets, snare, root, fast DD's.  Chanter/Mage also great, not as good in terms of fast mob drops, but close.  Druid/Mage is okay.  Wizzie/Mage doesn't have as much defense or healing, but is super fast in Mob drops which almost makes up for it.<br>
<br>
